1.001000   2026-07-03

  - First independent Net-Nostr-Core release, split from Net-Nostr
  - Provide core protocol and NIP tooling
  - Make AnyEvent::HTTP optional for Core and lazy-load it only for
    Net::Nostr::Identifier network lookup and verification
  - Recommend AnyEvent::HTTP for Core installs; the Net::Nostr shim keeps it
    as a hard dependency for the full historical install
  - Remove support for unrecommended NIPs 15, 28, 72, and 90, including
    Net::Nostr::Marketplace, Net::Nostr::Channel, Net::Nostr::Community, and
    Net::Nostr::DVM
  - Use Makefile.PL as the single dependency source of truth
  - Fix NIP-01 signature interoperability: sign and verify BIP-340 Schnorr
    signatures over the 32 raw bytes of the event id, not over its
    hex-string representation. Previously Net::Nostr::Key->sign_event,
    Net::Nostr::Event->validate/verify_sig, and Net::Nostr::Zap signed and
    verified over the ASCII hex id, so the library only interoperated with
    itself: it rejected events signed by standard Nostr implementations and
    produced signatures those implementations rejected. Events signed with
    the previous behavior are no longer valid and must be re-signed.
